00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:14,469
Grey, Yang, and myself.

768
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:15,776
Well, where are they, then?

769
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:18,027
They can formally present
their offer to you tomorrow

770
00:33:18,096 --> 00:33:20,230
if you hold off on
this sale to Pegasus.

771
00:33:20,282 --> 00:33:21,509
No, you can't do that.

772
00:33:21,533 --> 00:33:22,677
You can't make Pegasus wait...

773
00:33:22,701 --> 00:33:24,167
You all have a choice here.

774
00:33:24,236 --> 00:33:26,453
You can either be
responsible for consigning

775
00:33:26,521 --> 00:33:28,621
this world-class hospital
to the scrap heap...

776
00:33:28,690 --> 00:33:29,934
There's no choice. Or...

777
00:33:29,958 --> 00:33:31,102
It's not a deal.

778
00:33:31,126 --> 00:33:32,670
Or you can partner
with the doctors

779
00:33:32,694 --> 00:33:34,222
who made this place what it was

780
00:33:34,246 --> 00:33:35,828
and see what it can be.

781
00:33:35,897 --> 00:33:37,542
The Pegasus deal went away once.

782
00:33:37,566 --> 00:33:40,233
If it goes away again,
you have nothing,

783
00:33:40,302 --> 00:33:42,218
no severance packages,

784
00:33:42,287 --> 00:33:43,920
no paying off creditors.

785
00:33:43,972 --> 00:33:45,733
You can't make
payroll next week.

786
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:46,940
Nothing.

787
00:33:47,009 --> 00:33:48,958
All we need is one day.

788
00:33:49,028 --> 00:33:50,260
One day.

789
00:33:58,720 --> 00:33:59,819
Do you see them?

790
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:01,305
There.

791
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:04,548
Do they look happy?

792
00:34:04,576 --> 00:34:05,742
I can't tell.

793
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:07,938
Sad?

794
00:34:08,597 --> 00:34:09,677
I can't tell.

795
00:34:30,135 --> 00:34:31,375
I got them to wait.

796
00:34:31,436 --> 00:34:32,947
The board is gonna
wait for one more day.

797
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:34,098
You can make your pitch.

798
00:34:34,122 --> 00:34:35,322
I did it.

799
00:34:35,357 --> 00:34:36,389
We didn't.

800
00:34:36,475 --> 00:34:38,608
Crest met with
Richard, liked him,

801
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:40,260
liked all of us,

802
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:42,545
then he said no.

803
00:34:42,614 --> 00:34:44,430
Said he just wasn't feeling it.

804
00:34:49,788 --> 00:34:51,254
So it's over.

805
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,141
It's over.

806
00:35:04,719 --> 00:35:05,952
Dr. Kepner?

807
00:35:06,021 --> 00:35:07,537
Andy's awake.

808
00:35:07,606 --> 00:35:09,584
He's got some questions, and
I couldn't track down Dr. Hunt.

809
00:35:09,608 --> 00:35:11,808
Okay. I will be right there.

810
00:35:12,478 --> 00:35:14,427
I just needed some air.

811
00:35:15,763 --> 00:35:18,998
Can I ask you something?

812
00:35:19,067 --> 00:35:21,562
You want to know how
something like this could happen?

813
00:35:21,586 --> 00:35:23,085
I don't know.

814
00:35:27,258 --> 00:35:29,793
I guess I have to believe

815
00:35:29,861 --> 00:35:32,295
that everything
happens for a reason.

816
00:35:32,364 --> 00:35:35,164
It's all part of some plan,

817
00:35:35,217 --> 00:35:37,617
and you're supposed
to learn something.

818
00:35:41,789 --> 00:35:44,591
You lose a patient because
you forget to check their airway,

819
00:35:44,659 --> 00:35:46,254
you don't make
that mistake again.

820
00:35:46,278 --> 00:35:47,510
You fail your boards

821
00:35:47,578 --> 00:35:49,891
'cause you're too busy
sleeping with your best friend,

822
00:35:49,915 --> 00:35:51,480
maybe you stop doing that.

823
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:54,433
The hospital you
call home shuts down

824
00:35:54,502 --> 00:35:56,280
just when you're
finally starting to feel

825
00:35:56,304 --> 00:35:58,704
like you've got
your life together...

826
00:36:00,892 --> 00:36:03,726
Actually, I was gonna ask
for a letter of recommendation.

827
00:36:06,597 --> 00:36:07,831
Oh.

828
00:36:10,335 --> 00:36:13,069
But I could probably
ask someone else.

829
00:36:13,772 --> 00:36:15,505
That might be best.

830
00:36:23,515 --> 00:36:25,693
Go on home, Brooks.
I'll take it from here.

831
00:36:25,717 --> 00:36:27,877
If it's all the same,
Dr. Bailey, I'd prefer to stay.

832
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:30,420
Suit yourself.

833
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:39,323
What's wrong with your face?

834
00:36:39,347 --> 00:36:40,747
You're right.

835
00:36:40,816 --> 00:36:43,083
You are the heart
of the hospital.

836
00:36:45,220 --> 00:36:46,786
I was, Brooks.

837
00:36:48,857 --> 00:36:49,906
Was.

838
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,531
We're not buying a house. Hmm.

839
00:37:03,555 --> 00:37:04,899
Well, we're not
buying a hospital.

840
00:37:04,923 --> 00:37:06,105
We could buy a house.

841
00:37:06,174 --> 00:37:09,241
Or build one.

842
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:11,439
We don't even know where
we're gonna be in six months.

843
00:37:11,463 --> 00:37:15,531
So we build it in
Chicago or Miami

844
00:37:15,601 --> 00:37:17,583
or New York.

845
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:19,018
We have each other,

846
00:37:19,104 --> 00:37:21,704
and we have a
beautiful baby so...

847
00:37:21,773 --> 00:37:23,873
We can go wherever we want.

848
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,896
Probably want to sell
Mark's place, right?

849
00:37:32,066 --> 00:37:34,200
Probably.

850
00:37:39,273 --> 00:37:40,974
We don't have to
move yet, do we?

851
00:37:41,893 --> 00:37:42,993
No.

852
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:45,528
Not yet.

853
00:37:50,969 --> 00:37:53,403
Vermouth?

854
00:37:53,472 --> 00:37:56,106
That'll have to do.

855
00:37:56,174 --> 00:37:58,858
Oh, and now you're
stealing my freakin' booze.

856
00:37:58,927 --> 00:38:00,204
It's just vermouth. Shut up.

857
00:38:00,228 --> 00:38:02,173
You don't get to
make stupid little jokes.

858
00:38:02,197 --> 00:38:03,975
We had a good
thing going, all of us.

859
00:38:03,999 --> 00:38:05,693
And now people
are losing their jobs,

860
00:38:05,717 --> 00:38:06,983
and it's your fault.

861
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:09,097
We were trying to
buy the stupid hospital.

862
00:38:09,121 --> 00:38:10,536
We were trying to help,

863
00:38:11,739 --> 00:38:13,089
and we screwed up.

864
00:38:13,859 --> 00:38:15,191
I'm sorry.

865
00:38:20,882 --> 00:38:22,248
Oh, well...

866
00:38:27,222 --> 00:38:29,739
40-year-old Scotch.
A patient gave it to me.

867
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:31,240
Now you're gonna sit down

868
00:38:31,310 --> 00:38:33,225
and you're gonna
freakin' talk to me.

869
00:38:40,519 --> 00:38:42,796
Oh, Derek, it's over.
Enough. You have to stop.

870
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:45,688
Yeah, I know. Ross asked me to
write a letter of recommendation.

871
00:38:45,757 --> 00:38:48,324
And I'm gonna do them
for each of the interns.

872
00:38:51,113 --> 00:38:53,646
Did you do one
for Heather Brooks?

873
00:38:53,715 --> 00:38:55,193
Who? Mousy.

874
00:38:55,217 --> 00:38:56,849
Oh, no. Not yet.

875
00:38:56,918 --> 00:38:57,984
I will.

876
00:39:04,392 --> 00:39:06,859
They were trying to buy
the hospital themselves.

877
00:39:06,928 --> 00:39:09,368
They... They just
needed more money.

878
00:39:10,632 --> 00:39:13,266
They couldn't get it in time.

879
00:39:13,335 --> 00:39:15,501
Well, what are you gonna do now?

880
00:39:16,638 --> 00:39:19,572
Well, I heard
Boston's awfully nice.

881
00:39:19,641 --> 00:39:22,525
That thought has crossed
my mind a time or two.

882
00:39:22,594 --> 00:39:25,127
I just didn't want to be pushy.

883
00:39:25,197 --> 00:39:26,997
That hardly sounds like you.

884
00:39:33,338 --> 00:39:36,038
I poured so much of my
life into Seattle Grace.

885
00:39:38,343 --> 00:39:40,020
Always seemed like
a foregone conclusion

886
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:42,444
that I'd end my career
there, and I just...

887
00:39:47,202 --> 00:39:49,335
I'm not ready to retire yet.

888
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:54,557
I never thought it would
be gone before I was.

889
00:39:56,645 --> 00:39:58,694
How much money did they need?

890
00:40:14,329 --> 00:40:16,023
What are you guys... Oh.

891
00:40:16,047 --> 00:40:17,663
Folks!

892
00:40:17,732 --> 00:40:18,814
You're right on time.

893
00:40:23,638 --> 00:40:24,837
Come on.

894
00:40:30,845 --> 00:40:32,862
Mom, come on. What is happening?

895
00:40:32,931 --> 00:40:34,575
Have a seat. I'm
about to tell you.

896
00:40:34,599 --> 00:40:37,801
<i>There's a reason surgeons
are willing to roll the dice</i>

897
00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:40,920
<i>on a risky, go-for-broke,</i>

898
00:40:40,988 --> 00:40:43,155
<i>point-of-no-return surgery</i>

899
00:40:43,224 --> 00:40:46,042
<i>with potentially
devastating consequences.</i>

900
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:47,493
Ladies and gentlemen,

901
00:40:47,562 --> 00:40:50,062
Dr. Webber's brought
to my attention the fact

902
00:40:50,148 --> 00:40:53,466
that all of you have been
looking for an investor

903
00:40:53,535 --> 00:40:55,434
to partner with
you in purchasing

904
00:40:55,503 --> 00:40:58,104
Seattle Grace-Mercy
West Hospital.

905
00:40:58,173 --> 00:41:01,891
It is my pleasure to tell you

906
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:05,261
that the Harper Avery
Foundation would like very much

907
00:41:05,330 --> 00:41:06,979
to take you up on that offer.

908
00:41:07,048 --> 00:41:08,692
What?

909
00:41:08,716 --> 00:41:12,151
We have only one
condition. Only one.

910
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:15,332
Since the foundation will be
putting up the majority of the funds,

911
00:41:15,356 --> 00:41:19,258
we would like a
representative of our choosing

912
00:41:19,327 --> 00:41:21,844
to sit on your
board of directors.

913
00:41:21,913 --> 00:41:23,891
Well, yeah...

914
00:41:23,915 --> 00:41:27,249
My dears, we only have a
couple of hours to make this bid.

915
00:41:27,319 --> 00:41:28,829
Do you want to
do this thing or not?

916
00:41:28,853 --> 00:41:30,414
Yes. Of course. Okay, yes.

917
00:41:30,438 --> 00:41:31,570
<i>Sometimes...</i>

918
00:41:31,639 --> 00:41:32,749
Yeah. Yes.

919
00:41:32,773 --> 00:41:33,839
<i>It works.</i>

920
00:41:36,711 --> 00:41:38,511
Wow.

921
00:41:43,818 --> 00:41:45,835
Wait, you woke up
me at the crack of dawn

922
00:41:45,904 --> 00:41:48,182
to tell me you're coming to Seattle
to be my boss? That doesn't...

923
00:41:48,206 --> 00:41:50,290
Oh, no, no, sweetheart.
You misunderstood.

924
00:41:50,358 --> 00:41:53,626
The foundation is electing
you as our representative.

925
00:41:53,694 --> 00:41:54,972
We're the majority shareholder.

926
00:41:54,996 --> 00:41:57,980
That means you are in charge.

927
00:41:58,049 --> 00:41:59,660
Wait. What?

928
00:41:59,684 --> 00:42:01,834
Now give your
mama a kiss, Jackson.

929
00:42:01,902 --> 00:42:03,969
She just bought you a hospital.

930
00:42:05,307 --> 00:42:06,307
Hmm.
